com.xilinx.rapidwright.device

Class Node

  • Object
    • com.xilinx.rapidwright.device.Node
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    WireInterface, Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NetTools.NodeTree, RouteNode, RouterHelper.NodeWithPrev

    public class Node
extends Object
implements WireInterface, Serializable
    This class represents a reference to the notion of a node in Vivado, which is an electrically connected set of Wires that can span tiles. As nodes are a collection of wires, their reference point is a base wire. Created on: Jul 5, 2016
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • getWiresInNode

        public static Wire[] getWiresInNode(Tile tile,
                                    int wire)
        Creates an array of wires that correspond to the node of the provided wire reference.

        Vivado Tcl:

        get_wires -of [get_nodes -of [get_wires -of [get_tiles $tile] -filter ID_IN_TILE_TYPE==$wire]]

        Parameters:
        tile - Tile of the reference wire to get
        wire - The wire of the reference tile to get
        Returns:
        A list of wires that combine to make the node. It will include the referenced wire provided as input.
        Since:
        2018.2.0
